PARAM.DESC: Enables the output of a COFF debug file.

OPTION.NAME: +EA
OPTION.DESC: Show all error messages and all warnings

OPTION.NAME: +V
OPTION.DESC: Show compiler version (no compile is done)

OPTION.NAME: +Q
OPTION.DESC: Show all valid devices in database (no compile is done)

OPTION.NAME: -T
OPTION.DESC: Do not generate a tree file)

OPTION.NAME: -P
OPTION.DESC: Close compile window after compile is complete

OPTION.NAME: +P
OPTION.DESC: Keep compiler window open according to param. +P[xx|N|E]

OPTION.NAME: +Z
OPTION.DESC: Keep scratch files on disk after compile

OPTION.NAME: I=
OPTION.DESC: Set include directory search path: I="c:\picc\examples;c:\picc\myincludes"

OPTION.NAME: I+=
OPTION.DESC: Same as I="..." Except the path list is appended to the current list

OPTION.NAME: +ICD
OPTION.DESC: Compile for use with an ICD

OPTION.NAME: +STDOUT
OPTION.DESC: Outputs errors to STDOUT (for use with third party editors)

OPTION.NAME: +SETUP
OPTION.DESC: Install CCSC into MPLAB (no compile is done)

OPTION.NAME: sourceline=
OPTION.DESC: Injects a source line at the start of a source file: sourceline="#include <16F887.h>"
